{
  "page": "Harma Dogshead",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table class=\"infobox\" style=\"min-width:22em;max-width:32em;border-collapse:separate;border-spacing:3px\"><tbody><tr><th colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;font-size:125%;font-weight:bold;font-weight:bold; background: none; line-height: 1.1em;\">Harma Dogshead</th></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" class=\"infobox-image\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<a href=\"/index.php/File:Harma_Dogshead_by_henning.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Harma Dogshead by henning.jpg\" src=\"/images/thumb/2/2e/Harma_Dogshead_by_henning.jpg/300px-Harma_Dogshead_by_henning.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"225\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/2/2e/Harma_Dogshead_by_henning.jpg/450px-Harma_Dogshead_by_henning.jpg 1.5x, /images/2/2e/Harma_Dogshead_by_henning.jpg 2x\" /></a><div>Harma Dogshead by Henning Ludvigsen © Fantasy Flight Games</div></td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<hr /></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Aliases</th><td>\n<div class=\"plainlist\"><ul><li>Harma the Dogshead</li><li>Harma Dogshead</li></ul></div></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Allegiance</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Mance_Rayder\" title=\"Mance Rayder\">Mance Rayder</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Culture</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Free_folk\" title=\"Free folk\">Free folk</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Died</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/300_AC\" title=\"300 AC\">300&#160;AC</a><br /><a href=\"/index.php/Battle_beneath_the_Wall\" title=\"Battle beneath the Wall\">The Wall</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Books</th><td>\n<div class=\"plainlist\"><ul><li><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Clash_of_Kings\" title=\"A Clash of Kings\">A Clash of Kings</a></i> (mentioned)</li><li><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Storm_of_Swords\" title=\"A Storm of Swords\">A Storm of Swords</a></i> (appears)</li><li><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Dance_with_Dragons\" title=\"A Dance with Dragons\">A Dance with Dragons</a></i> (mentioned)</li></ul></div></td></tr></tbody></table> \n<p><b>Harma Dogshead</b>,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos7.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos7.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos15.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos15.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> also known as <b>Harma the Dogshead</b><sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok43.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok43.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> and <b>Dogshead</b>,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasosappendix.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasosappendix.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> is a known <a href=\"/index.php/Free_folk\" title=\"Free folk\">free folk</a> raider.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos7.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos7.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> She has a brother, <a href=\"/index.php/Halleck\" title=\"Halleck\">Halleck</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasosappendix.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasosappendix.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Appearance\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Appearance</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#History\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">History</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Recent_Events\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Recent Events</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#A_Clash_of_Kings\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>A Clash of Kings</i></span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#A_Storm_of_Swords\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.2</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>A Storm of Swords</i></span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-6\"><a href=\"#A_Dance_with_Dragons\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.3</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>A Dance with Dragons</i></span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-7\"><a href=\"#Quotes_by_Harma\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Quotes by Harma</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-8\"><a href=\"#Quotes_about_Harma\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Quotes about Harma</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-9\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">6</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Appearance\">Appearance</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Harma_Dogshead&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Appearance\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<dl><dd><i>See also: <a href=\"/index.php/Category:Images_of_Harma\" title=\"Category:Images of Harma\">Images of Harma</a></i></dd></dl>\n<p>Squat and round, Harma Dogshead is a huge woman with white cheeks.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos15.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos15.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Harma hates <a href=\"/index.php/Dog\" title=\"Dog\">dogs</a>, and she kills one every fortnight to create a new totem for her banner.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos15.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos15.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> She owns pigs.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd10.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd10.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Harma_Dogshead&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: History\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:352px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Harma_vs_Rattleshirt.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/f/fa/Harma_vs_Rattleshirt.jpg/350px-Harma_vs_Rattleshirt.jpg\" width=\"350\" height=\"217\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/f/fa/Harma_vs_Rattleshirt.jpg/525px-Harma_vs_Rattleshirt.jpg 1.5x, /images/thumb/f/fa/Harma_vs_Rattleshirt.jpg/700px-Harma_vs_Rattleshirt.jpg 2x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Harma_vs_Rattleshirt.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Harma and <a href=\"/index.php/Rattleshirt\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Rattleshirt\">Rattleshirt</a>, by Jon Neimeister © Fantasy Flight Games</div></div></div>\n<p>Before <a href=\"/index.php/Mance_Rayder\" title=\"Mance Rayder\">Mance Rayder</a> made peace between them, Harma once warred with <a href=\"/index.php/Rattleshirt\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Rattleshirt\">Rattleshirt</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos15.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos15.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Harma has become a well known raider among the brothers of the <a href=\"/index.php/Night%27s_Watch\" title=\"Night&#39;s Watch\">Night's Watch</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos7.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos7.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Recent_Events\">Recent Events</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Harma_Dogshead&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Recent Events\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Clash_of_Kings\"><i>A Clash of Kings</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Harma_Dogshead&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Clash of Kings\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>Harma the Dogshead is among the leaders of <a href=\"/index.php/Mance_Rayder\" title=\"Mance Rayder\">Mance Rayder</a>'s army that the <a href=\"/index.php/Night%27s_Watch\" title=\"Night&#39;s Watch\">Night's Watch</a> are wary of.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok43.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok43.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Storm_of_Swords\"><i>A Storm of Swords</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Harma_Dogshead&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Storm of Swords\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>Harma leads the van of the <a href=\"/index.php/Free_folk\" title=\"Free folk\">free folk</a> army that marches south down the <a href=\"/index.php/Milkwater\" title=\"Milkwater\">Milkwater</a>. <a href=\"/index.php/Goady\" title=\"Goady\">Goady</a> creeps up on her camp and spots her with five hundred horsemen. <a href=\"/index.php/Thoren_Smallwood\" title=\"Thoren Smallwood\">Thoren Smallwood</a> convinces <a href=\"/index.php/Tumberjon\" title=\"Tumberjon\">Tumberjon</a> not to shoot Harma with an arrow.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos0.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_6-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos0.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Harma is present when the free folk discover the remains of the camp of the Night's Watch following the <a href=\"/index.php/Fight_at_the_Fist\" title=\"Fight at the Fist\">fight at the Fist</a>. She is skeptical when <a href=\"/index.php/Jon_Snow\" title=\"Jon Snow\">Jon Snow</a> reveals that the <a href=\"/index.php/Great_ranging\" title=\"Great ranging\">great ranging</a> is led by <a href=\"/index.php/Jeor_Mormont\" title=\"Jeor Mormont\">Jeor Mormont</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Lord_Commander_of_the_Night%27s_Watch\" title=\"Lord Commander of the Night&#39;s Watch\">Lord Commander of the Night's Watch</a>, and she smirks when <a href=\"/index.php/Ygritte\" title=\"Ygritte\">Ygritte</a> says she has been sleeping with Jon.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos15.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos15.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>During the wildling assault on the <a href=\"/index.php/Wall\" title=\"Wall\">Wall</a>, Harma is spotted near <a href=\"/index.php/Woodswatch-by-the-Pool\" title=\"Woodswatch-by-the-Pool\">Woodswatch-by-the-Pool</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos48.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_7-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos48.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Harma returns from her raids and feints to the main encampment of Mance's army by <a href=\"/index.php/Castle_Black\" title=\"Castle Black\">Castle Black</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos73.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_8-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos73.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup> When Jon arrives at Mance's tent, she urges Mance to kill him.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos73.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_8-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos73.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup> When <a href=\"/index.php/Rangers\" title=\"Rangers\">rangers</a> from <a href=\"/index.php/Eastwatch-by-the-Sea\" title=\"Eastwatch-by-the-Sea\">Eastwatch-by-the-Sea</a> appear, Mance has Harma ride against them with thirty raiders. The rangers are followed by the <a href=\"/index.php/Southron\" title=\"Southron\">southron</a> host of <a href=\"/index.php/Stannis_Baratheon\" title=\"Stannis Baratheon\">Stannis Baratheon</a>, however, and one column of armored <a href=\"/index.php/Knight\" title=\"Knight\">knights</a> smashes Harma. Later in the <a href=\"/index.php/Battle_beneath_the_Wall\" title=\"Battle beneath the Wall\">battle beneath the Wall</a>, Jon sees someone waving Harma's head on a pole.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos73.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_8-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos73.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Dance_with_Dragons\"><i>A Dance with Dragons</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Harma_Dogshead&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Dance with Dragons\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>Harma's brother <a href=\"/index.php/Halleck\" title=\"Halleck\">Halleck</a> kneels before Stannis and yields her pigs.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd10.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd10.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Quotes_by_Harma\">Quotes by Harma</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Harma_Dogshead&amp;action=edit&amp;section=7\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Quotes by Harma\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:352px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Ryan_Barger_The_Wildling_Horde.png\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/2/24/Ryan_Barger_The_Wildling_Horde.png/350px-Ryan_Barger_The_Wildling_Horde.png\" width=\"350\" height=\"231\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/2/24/Ryan_Barger_The_Wildling_Horde.png/525px-Ryan_Barger_The_Wildling_Horde.png 1.5x, /images/2/24/Ryan_Barger_The_Wildling_Horde.png 2x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Ryan_Barger_The_Wildling_Horde.png\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Harma in the host of <a href=\"/index.php/Mance_Rayder\" title=\"Mance Rayder\">Mance Rayder</a>, by Ryan Barger © Fantasy Flight Games</div></div></div>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p><b>Harma</b>: Kill him. Send his body back up in that cage o' theirs and tell them to send us someone else. I'll keep his head for my standard. A <a href=\"/index.php/Turncloak\" title=\"Turncloak\">turncloak</a>'s worse than a <a href=\"/index.php/Dog\" title=\"Dog\">dog</a>.<br />\n</p><p><b>Varamyr</b>: I warned you he was false. I never did like the smell o' him.<br />\n<b>Tormund</b>: Pull in your claws, <a href=\"/index.php/Skinchanger\" title=\"Skinchanger\">beastling</a>. <a href=\"/index.php/Jon_Snow\" title=\"Jon Snow\">The lad's</a> here to hear. You lay a paw on him, might be I'll take me that <a href=\"/index.php/Shadowskin\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Shadowskin\">shadowskin</a> cloak I been wanting.<br />\n</p>\n<b>Harma</b>: Tormund Crowlover. You are a great sack o' wind, old man.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos73.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_8-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos73.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup><p class=\"mw-empty-elt\"></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;Harma, <a href=\"/index.php/Varamyr_Sixskins\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Varamyr Sixskins\">Varamyr Sixskins</a>, and <a href=\"/index.php/Tormund_Giantsbane\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Tormund Giantsbane\">Tormund Giantsbane</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Quotes_about_Harma\">Quotes about Harma</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Harma_Dogshead&amp;action=edit&amp;section=8\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Quotes about Harma\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p><b>Kedge</b>: Harma the Dogshead has the van, the poxy bitch. <a href=\"/index.php/Goady\" title=\"Goady\">Goady</a> crept up on her camp and saw her plain by the fire. That fool <a href=\"/index.php/Tumberjon\" title=\"Tumberjon\">Tumberjon</a> wanted to pick her off with an arrow, but <a href=\"/index.php/Thoren_Smallwood\" title=\"Thoren Smallwood\">Smallwood</a> had better sense.<br />\n</p><p><b>Chett</b>: How many were there, could you tell?<br />\n</p>\n<b>Kedge</b>: Many and more. Twenty, thirty thousand, we didn't stay to count. Harma had five hundred in the van, every one ahorse.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasosprologue.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_9-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasosprologue.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-9\">&#91;9&#93;</a></sup><p class=\"mw-empty-elt\"></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Kedge_Whiteye\" title=\"Kedge Whiteye\">Kedge Whiteye</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Chett\" title=\"Chett\">Chett</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>There was Harma Dogshead, a squat keg of a woman with cheeks like slabs of white meat, who hated <a href=\"/index.php/Dog\" title=\"Dog\">dogs</a> and killed one every fortnight to make a fresh head for her banner; earless <a href=\"/index.php/Styr\" title=\"Styr\">Styr</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Magnar_of_Thenn\" title=\"Magnar of Thenn\">Magnar of Thenn</a>, whose <a href=\"/index.php/Thenns\" title=\"Thenns\">own people</a> thought him more god than lord; <a href=\"/index.php/Varamyr_Sixskins\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Varamyr Sixskins\">Varamyr Sixskins</a>, a small mouse of a man whose steed was a savage white <a href=\"/index.php/Snow_bear\" title=\"Snow bear\">snow bear</a> that stood thirteen feet tall on its hind legs.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos15.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos15.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;thoughts of <a href=\"/index.php/Jon_Snow\" title=\"Jon Snow\">Jon Snow</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>Behind her stood her banner bearer, holding a pole with a <a href=\"/index.php/Dog\" title=\"Dog\">dog</a>'s head on it, fresh enough to still be leaking blood.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos15.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos15.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;thoughts of <a href=\"/index.php/Jon_Snow\" title=\"Jon Snow\">Jon Snow</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p><b>Ygritte</b>: You call us thieves, but at least a thief has t' be brave and clever and quick. A kneeler only has t' kneel.<br />\n<b>Jon</b>: Harma and the <a href=\"/index.php/Bag_of_Bones\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Bag of Bones\">Bag of Bones</a> don't come raiding for fish and apples. They steal swords and axes. Spices, <a href=\"/index.php/Silk\" title=\"Silk\">silks</a>, and furs. They grab every coin and ring and jeweled cup they can find, casks of <a href=\"/index.php/Wine\" title=\"Wine\">wine</a> in summer and casks of beef in winter, and they take women in any season and carry them off <a href=\"/index.php/Beyond_the_Wall\" title=\"Beyond the Wall\">beyond the Wall</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos41.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_10-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos41.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-10\">&#91;10&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Ygritte\" title=\"Ygritte\">Ygritte</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Jon_Snow\" title=\"Jon Snow\">Jon Snow</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p><b>Edd</b>: Just last night I dreamt I was pissing off the <a href=\"/index.php/Wall\" title=\"Wall\">Wall</a> when someone decided to give <a href=\"/index.php/Horn_of_Joramun\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Horn of Joramun\">the horn</a> a toot. Not that I'm complaining. It was better than my old dream, where Harma Dogshead was feeding me to her pigs.<br />\n</p><p><b>Jon</b>: Harma's dead.<br />\n</p>\n<b>Edd</b>: But not the pigs. They look at me the way <a href=\"/index.php/Samwell_Tarly\" title=\"Samwell Tarly\">Slayer</a> used to look at ham.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd10.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd10.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup><p class=\"mw-empty-elt\"></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Eddison_Tollett\" title=\"Eddison Tollett\">Eddison Tollett</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Jon_Snow\" title=\"Jon Snow\">Jon Snow</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Harma_Dogshead&amp;action=edit&amp;section=9\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\" style=\"-webkit-column-width:200px; -moz-column-width:200px; column-width:200px; -webkit-column-count:2; -moz-column-count:2; column-count:2;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rasos7.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rasos7.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\">1.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rasos7.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\">1.1</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rasos7.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-2\">1.2</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Storm_of_Swords\" title=\"A Storm of Swords\">A Storm of Swords</a></i>, <a href=\"/index.php/A_Storm_of_Swords-Chapter_7\" title=\"A Storm of Swords-Chapter 7\">Chapter 7</a>, Jon I.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rasos15.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rasos15.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\">2.0</a></sup> <sup><